This paper is about Click-Through Rate (CTR) prediction, which is a common problem in the field of machine learning and information retrieval. The paper proposes a novel Field-Leveraged Embedding Network (FLEN) for CTR prediction, which involves techniques such as bi-interaction pooling and dropout. These techniques are commonly used in the sub-fields of machine learning and deep learning, which are covered by the arXiv categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper discusses the scalability of the proposed approach, which is relevant to the sub-fields of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.DB (Databases). Therefore, the most likely arXiv categories for this paper are cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.CR, and cs.DB, in that order.
